values:
Things with classes are going well.&nbsp; Attention grabbing professors and interesting&nbsp;subjects should make for a great semester.&nbsp; Living with the girls is awesome.&nbsp; I'm thrilled that our latest addition to our familia is fitting in well.&nbsp; One of our guy friends, who I&nbsp;used to like, is really taking a liking to her *wink wink (only because I&nbsp;know she's going to read this in a few hours).&nbsp; It's really weird to see him flirt with someone, but I'm incredibly happy for her.&nbsp; It just makes me feel that all my horrible attempts to win his affection last year were obviously in vain since her and I are so different.&nbsp; It just goes to show that you can't force feelings like that for someone---I deliberately tried and she simply walked in the room.&nbsp; I love learning lessons a year later....couldn't somebody have told me I looked like an ass 10 months ago??&nbsp; 

As far as my boy department is concerned:&nbsp; one guy is too busy with his career right now (which I&nbsp;think is great) but we haven't had any time with just the two of us yet.&nbsp; I'm worried that this could be really great but unless we are given an opportunity for it to grow and let a relationship start to form, I fear that it will simply stall out on this plateau that it has reached.&nbsp; The other guy I see all the time.&nbsp; Unfortunately, he is mending a broken heart at the moment.&nbsp; I don't want to make a move out of fear that if anything I&nbsp;will be the rebound girl.&nbsp; I've always felt something between us--I&nbsp;passed it off as nothingworth noting (probably because he was always with the girlfriend) but my friends have always said differently.&nbsp; He's the perfect mix of two things I love:&nbsp; theatre and sports, but I&nbsp;really don't want to jump the gun.

I feel like I'm stuck at a fork in the road.&nbsp; I've lost my map and the only compass I&nbsp;have is my heart which quite frankly doesn't know what to do.&nbsp; I've decided that I've already come this far and now it's up to them to meet me the other half of the way.&nbsp; I'm not afraid of making the journey on my own but it would be awfully nice to have some company.

Words can barely express the summer it's been.&nbsp; I have truly grown--something I don't think I've been able to say in a while.&nbsp; In 4 months so much has changed, hopefully for the better.&nbsp; I'm one step closer to knowing the real me and to knowing what I want, in many aspects of my life.&nbsp; Thanks go out to those that have crossed my path most recently.&nbsp; Some have already left a definable mark.&nbsp; For others, I think I will need to leave Venice and let go before I can realize the impact you have had on my life.&nbsp; Regardless if the experiences were good or bad, I thank you.&nbsp; People never cease to surprise me.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Being home this summer has been great.&nbsp; I've worked my ass off and am need of a vacation--going back to Orlando is precisely what the doctor ordered.&nbsp; It's time to move on.&nbsp; To continue to grow.&nbsp; To live freely and take on new adventures.&nbsp; Day break can't come soon enough.

It's been real.&nbsp;
xoxo-"Tomorrow, and tomorrow, and tomorrow."

So many new twists and&nbsp;turns have come into my life lately.&nbsp; Surprises.&nbsp; Friends&nbsp;calling unexpectedly.&nbsp; Things with mom getting back to normal.&nbsp; A different guy.&nbsp; I know that I have grown and changed as a person while I was gone--and the people back home&nbsp;have grown just as much.&nbsp; As for now--I am content with who I am--and more importantly who I am becoming.&nbsp; Being surrounded by the people I love is icing on the cake.
xoxo-having&nbsp;my cake and eating it too!&nbsp;
p.s. enjoying a delicious chocolate milkshake at Bogeys always seems to do the trick.&nbsp; It was the perfect ending to a perfect day. :)
